Work Experience

ATDOnline/TireProsOnline/NTDConnect

I undertook a multifaceted role in elevating the digital footprint of ATDOnline, TireProsOnline, and NTDConnect, our primary B2B platforms. This encompassed adeptly overseeing marketing content, serving as the go-to authority for all CMS-related matters, and taking the lead on diverse frontend initiatives. My primary objects included:

  • Collaborated closely with backend developers to design and develop dynamic frontend experiences that improve user interactions and content delivery.
  • Partnered with designers to create engaging landing pages to enhance user engagement.
  • Developed complex and targeted marketing experiences to cater to diverse audience segments.
  • Designed and executed various A/B tests, including enhancements like new header menus and cart previews, to refine the UX/UI and boost user satisfaction.
  • Conducted A/B testing on marketing ads to refine advertising campaigns and maximize their effectiveness.
  • Implemented GA tagging and analytics on all content to gather insights and drive data-driven decision-making.
  • Assisted with SEO efforts, including image optimization and tagging, updating meta data, and selecting keywords to enhance website visibility and search rankings.
  • Implemented and managed marketing and sales data using ImpEx files, ensuring data consistency and accuracy.
  • Managed all product imagery and mapping within multiple systems to ensure accurate product listings.
  • Handled all user/location and site-level configurations, such as user/location restrictions, and overall site features.
  • Served as the primary onboarding resource for new team members, providing training and guidance on complex content management systems (CMS) and digital asset management (DAM) tools.

ATD.com

As the lead web producer and content manager, I oversaw all content updates through a dedicated CMS, ensuring that the site's information remained up-to-date and engaging. My contributions as the primary web producer were instrumental in maintaining the website's dynamic frontend content and CMS updates. My role included:

  • Managed and updated all content through a dedicated CMS to ensure its accuracy and relevance.
  • Acted as the go-to frontend developer for the creation of responsive landing pages, enhancing user experience.
  • Designed engaging homepage heroes for various events and campaigns, capturing the essence of each initiative.
  • Coordinated a complex press release process, which included ImpEx files to speed up production, as these were often given to us on a tight deadline.
  • Assisted with SEO efforts, including image optimization and tagging, updating meta data, and selecting keywords to enhance website visibility and search rankings.
  • Provided second-tier support for quick bug fixes, addressing issues promptly and facilitating their integration into the regular release schedule.
